+//!
+//! This test explores whether NPU can do useful work in parallel with GPU.
+//!
+//! Scenarios tested:
+//! 1. GPU-only baseline: Sequential GPU matmuls
+//! 2. GPU + NPU parallel: GPU does large matmul, NPU does small matmul simultaneously
+//! 3. Pipelined: GPU → NPU → GPU chain (simulating multi-stage inference)
+//!
+//! Real-world analogy:
+//! - GPU: Running main LLM (Qwen2.5-32B)
+//! - NPU: Running small classifier/embedder in parallel
+//!
+//! Expected outcome:
+//! - If NPU truly runs in parallel, total time < GPU time alone
+//! - If NPU blocks GPU, total time ≈ GPU time + NPU time
